     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>To the same Noble Earle, two Acrosticke Stanza's.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>Glory in you is like the Sun, which giues</l>
      <l>Eternall splendour, yet is often hid,</l>
      <l>Ore-shadow'd in some clime, when yet he liues</l>
      <l>Reviving still: the world cannot forbid</l>
      <l>Glory her beames; but like fires hid in night</l>
      <l>Expresse at last a more refulgent light.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Grace then the Muses, who can giue you light,</l>
      <l>Obliuion it selfe can neuer hide,</l>
      <l>Respect those Sacrifices, by whose might,</l>
      <l>Demigods soone are wholly Deifide:</l>
      <l>Onely giue pardon to me, who can giue</l>
      <l>Nothing else yet, to make you longer liue.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>A. H.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
